    • Method Detail

      • referenceTypeVariable

        public static Type referenceTypeVariable(String name)
        Type variable declarations intended to have bounds on other type variable declarations within the same parameterized declaration may specify those bounds by reference to the name of the other type variable. This method creates a placeholder type for this purpose, which will be substituted with the appropriate TypeVariable when the parameterized declaration is actualized into its definition. This is also useful as type variable declarations sometimes need to be self-referential in their bounds, whether directly or indirectly. Recursive data structures are difficult to capture naturally through immutable APIs, but referencing type variable declarations by name rather than by identity makes this a little simpler.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the type variable declaration to create a placeholder for
        Returns:
        a placeholder for a type variable of the given name

      • withAnnotations

        public TypeVariableSignature withAnnotations(Collection<? extends Annotation> annotations)
        Description copied from interface: AnnotatedSignature
        Derive a version of this declaration with the given annotations. Users should take care not to specify annotations which could not be applied to the declaration due to their Target, as there is no validation of applicability.

        Annotations already present on the receiving declaration will be replaced rather than appended.

        Specified by:
        withAnnotations in interface AnnotatedSignature<TypeVariableSignature>
        Parameters:
        annotations - the annotations with which to annotate this declaration
        Returns:
        a new declaration of the same type, and with the same content, but with the given annotations
